<paragraph blockId="144.[189,1399,1413,1548]" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hess" authorityYear="1964" box="[329,474,1414,1439]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Dermocoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="144" pageNumber="145" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[329,474,1414,1439]" italics="true" pageId="144" pageNumber="145">Dermocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with moderately large LAPs displaying a well-developed vertical striation on outer surface; up to three spurs on outer proximal and inner distal edges; up to six large spine articulations; ventral lobe merged with distalwards pointing tip of outer surface separating notches of spine articulations; ridge on inner side of LAPs slender, dorsal part not thickened.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
